Class B extends Class A and implements the functional interfaces. You can then define the implementations of the functional methods, `method1()` and `method2()`, within Class B.

Inside the `main()` function, you can create an instance of Class B (`instanceB`) and call both the normal method (`normalMethod()`) inherited from Class A, and the overridden functional methods (`method1()` and `method2()`).

